article.headline: Texas Southern 72, Alcorn State 49
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Sean Walker scored 13 points and Allen Lovett added 12 as Texas Southern beat Alcorn State 72-49 Saturday night. Texas Southern (5-5, 1-0 Southwestern Athletic) led for most of the game, building a 31-18 halftime lead despite shooting just 39 percent in the half. Dion Callans led Alcorn State (1-7, 0-1) with 15 points on 6-of-9 shooting from the field. Brian Jackson was the only other double-digit scorer for Alcorn with 10 points. Alcorn State lost 25 turnovers and couldn't recover from poor first-half shooting (7-of-22 from the field).
